&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paediatric unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse - Bank&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Paediatric Department at Walsall Healthcare NHS Trust consists of a 21 bedded General Paediatric Ward, which takes medical, surgical (including day case) and high dependency patients. A busy 6 bedded Paediatric Assessment Unit, an integrated Community Children’s team and Children’s Outpatients department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced enthusiastic, motivated children’s nurses who are able to work autonomously as well as part of a team; who is keen to develop and assist us to take the service forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require an individual with a team working approach who will be flexible to our service needs and passionate about delivering high quality care. In return we will offer a structured development package and the opportunity to be a valued member of our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As and when required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameFiona MullnerEmail addressfiona.mullner@walsallhealthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
